data.title: Morgan Cecil - 2021 - Women's Soccer
data.meta_description:
Morgan Cecil (14) Defender  - Cecil begins her fourth season with the Pfeiffer women's soccer program in 2020.

Spring 2021 (Junior) - Started all eight matches
data.text:
Cecil begins her fourth season with the Pfeiffer women's soccer program in 2020.

Spring 2021 (Junior) - Started all eight matches while playing defense. Had three shots with two being on goal.

2019 (Sophomore) - Started all 18 matches while playing defense. Notched a pair of assists on the year, with one coming in a 2-1 win over Edgewood and in the 1-0 USA South East Division-clinching win over Greensboro. Was named a USA South First Team selection on defense and was also an All-Eastern Division selection. Also named to the USA South All-Academic Team.

2018 (Freshman) - Appeared in 16 matches for the Falcons, firing six shots while playing mostly defense.

Prior to Pfeiffer - Played her high school soccer for coach Scott Marlega at Harmony High School. She scored 16 career goals during her prep career, including six during her senior year.

She was named Defensive Player of the Year all four years and All-County First-Team honors for three seasons. She was an All-County Second-Team selection during her freshman season.

She was also named Osceola County Player of the Year during her junior season.

Played her club soccer with the Florida Rush and Leon Florez.

Personal - Daughter of Brian Cecil and Lauren Swanson. Has one sibling, Conner (15).

Interesting Facts - The Office is her favorite TV show. Loves to swim.
